The paper deals with the analysis of signal-to-interference ratio (SIR) in cellular networks, which is a topic related to information theory (cs.IT) and network infrastructure (cs.NI). The paper also discusses the use of point processes to model base station tiers, which is a topic related to stochastic processes (cs.SI) and mathematical analysis (cs.MA). Finally, the paper proposes simple approximations for the SIR meta distribution, which is a topic related to probability theory (cs.PF).
